title: Mid-Autmn Festival 2015: Share Your Photos #MoonWSJ
text:
How are you celebrating the Mid-Autumn Festival? Share your experience of the holiday, also known as the Moon Festival, with The Wall Street Journal.
The Mid-Autumn Festival is when the moon as its brightest, and we’ll be highlighting readers’ photos of their celebrations from across the world. We would love to see lanterns, festival foods such as moon cakes, performances including lion and dragon dances, and eye-catching decorations... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
